  "texts": [
    "This condition plays a key role in Labourie's conjecture [Lab08], known to hold in rank 2 [Lab17, CTT19], but recently disproved for higher rank groups [SS22].",
    "See also [AL18,LM19].We now give a more detailed description of our results in the particularly relevant case of dimension 4.",
    "If dim N = 0, then the expanding soliton is a closed negative Einstein manifold (B 4, g B).",
    "For dim N = 1, the soliton is locally isometric to the product of R and a closed hyperbolic manifold (B 3, g B) (cf.",
    "[Lot10,Prop. 4.80])."
  ],
